# Release Version Alignment

- When preparing a release, always include **all publishable packages** in release/versioning steps so versions stay globally aligned across the monorepo.
- Do not prepare release bumps for only a subset of changed packages unless there is an explicit maintainer-approved exception for that release.
- If a release is requested and package selection is ambiguous, default to full publishable-package coverage.
